### VLab — ASA VPN Tests
### Tests VPN provisioning via /api/users/vpn (POST/DELETE)
### Internally SSH to Cisco ASA; responses stream ndjson
### Run: npm run dev (port 8800)

@base = http://localhost:8800
@api  = {{base}}/api

@adminEmail    = admin@vlab.com
@adminPassword = admin123

# Update these with real user IDs
@userId  = 4
@userId2 = 6


###
# ============================================================
# AUTH
# ============================================================

### Login — admin
POST {{api}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}",
  "password": "{{adminPassword}}"
}


###
# ============================================================
# VPN — single user
# ============================================================

### Enable VPN (ASA: username <email> password <vpnPassword>)
POST {{api}}/users/vpn
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userIds": [{{userId}}],
  "vpnPassword": "VpnPass@456"
}

###

### Disable VPN (ASA: no username <email>)
DELETE {{api}}/users/vpn
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userIds": [{{userId}}]
}


###
# ============================================================
# VPN — batch users
# ============================================================

### Enable VPN for multiple users
POST {{api}}/users/vpn
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userIds": [{{userId}}, {{userId2}}],
  "vpnPassword": "BatchVpn@789"
}

###

### Disable VPN for multiple users
DELETE {{api}}/users/vpn
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userIds": [{{userId}}, {{userId2}}]
}


###
# ============================================================
# Verify VPN state in DB
# ============================================================

### Check single user VPN status (vpn_enable + vpn_password fields)
GET {{api}}/users/{{userId}}

###

### List users in group to verify vpn_enable flags
GET {{api}}/users?groupId=2&page=1&pageSize=20
